{"data":[{"name":"87:1","price":"अपने सर्वोच्च पालनहार के नाम की पवित्रता का वर्णन करो।","arabic":"سَبِّحِ ٱسۡمَ رَبِّكَ ٱلۡأَعۡلَى","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5949,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"sabbiḥi is'ma rabbika al-aʿlā ","translations":["Glorify","(the) name","(of) your Lord","the Most High","(1)"],"transliterationArr":["sabbiḥi","is'ma","rabbika","al-aʿlā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,880],[2,880,1280],[3,1280,2150],[4,2150,3995]]}},{"name":"87:2","price":"जिसने पैदा किया और ठीक-ठीक बनाया।","arabic":"ٱلَّذِي خَلَقَ فَسَوَّىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5950,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"alladhī khalaqa fasawwā ","translations":["The One Who","created","then proportioned","(2)"],"transliterationArr":["alladhī","khalaqa","fasawwā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1020],[2,1020,1680],[3,1680,2915]]}},{"name":"87:3","price":"और जिसने (हर चीज़ को) अनुमानित किया, फिर मार्ग दिखाया।","arabic":"وَٱلَّذِي قَدَّرَ فَهَدَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5951,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-alladhī qaddara fahadā ","translations":["And the One Who","measured","then guided","(3)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-alladhī","qaddara","fahadā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1000],[2,1000,1840],[3,1840,2915]]}},{"name":"87:4","price":"और जिसने चारा उगाया।[1]","arabic":"وَٱلَّذِيٓ أَخۡرَجَ ٱلۡمَرۡعَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5952,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"1. (1-4) इन आयतों में जिस पालनहार ने अपने नाम की पवित्रता का वर्णन करने का आदेश दिया है उसका परिचय दिया गया है कि वह पालनहार है जिसने सभी को पैदा किया, फिर उनको संतुलित किया, और उनके लिए एक विशेष प्रकार का अनुमान बनाया जिसकी सीमा से नहीं निकल सकते, और उनके लिए उस कार्य को पूरा करने की राह दिखाई जिसके लिए उन्हें पैदा किया है।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-alladhī akhraja al-marʿā ","translations":["And the One Who","brings forth","the pasture","(4)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-alladhī","akhraja","al-marʿā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2600],[2,2600,3310],[3,3310,4535]]}},{"name":"87:5","price":"फिर उसे (सुखाकर) काले रंग का कूड़ा बना दिया।[2]","arabic":"فَجَعَلَهُۥ غُثَآءً أَحۡوَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5953,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"2. (4-5) इन आयतों में बताया गया है कि प्रत्येक कार्य अनुक्रम से धीरे-धीरे होते हैं। धरती के पौधे धीरे-धीरे गुंजान और हरे-भरे होते हैं। ऐसे ही मानवीय योग्यताएँ भी धीरे-धीरे पूरी होती हैं।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fajaʿalahu ghuthāan aḥwā ","translations":["And then makes it","stubble","dark","(5)"],"transliterationArr":["fajaʿalahu","ghuthāan","aḥwā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1250],[2,1250,3780],[3,3780,4795]]}},{"name":"87:6","price":"(ऐ नबी!) हम तुम्हें ऐसा पढ़ाएँगे कि तुम नहीं भूलोगे।","arabic":"سَنُقۡرِئُكَ فَلَا تَنسَىٰٓ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5954,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"sanuq'ri-uka falā tansā ","translations":["We will make you recite","so not","you will forget","(6)"],"transliterationArr":["sanuq'ri-uka","falā","tansā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1330],[2,1330,1980],[3,1980,3675]]}},{"name":"87:7","price":"परन्तु जो अल्लाह चाहे। निश्चय ही वह खुली बात को जानता है और उस बात को भी जो छिपी हुई है।","arabic":"إِلَّا مَا شَآءَ ٱللَّهُۚ إِنَّهُۥ يَعۡلَمُ ٱلۡجَهۡرَ وَمَا يَخۡفَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5955,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"illā mā shāa al-lahu innahu yaʿlamu al-jahra wamā yakhfā ","translations":["Except","what","wills","Allah","Indeed, He","knows","the manifest","and what","is hidden","(7)"],"transliterationArr":["illā","mā","shāa","al-lahu","innahu","yaʿlamu","al-jahra","wamā","yakhfā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,870],[2,870,1230],[3,1230,3290],[4,3290,6380],[5,6380,8130],[6,8130,9020],[7,9020,10030],[8,10030,10670],[9,10670,11645]]}},{"name":"87:8","price":"और हम तुम्हारे लिए सरल मार्ग आसान कर देंगे।[3]","arabic":"وَنُيَسِّرُكَ لِلۡيُسۡرَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5956,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"3. (6-8) इनमें नबी सल्लल्लाहु अलैहि व सल्लम को यह निर्देश दिया गया है कि इसकी चिंता न करें कि क़ुरआन मुझे कैसे याद होगा, इसे याद कराना हमारा काम है, और इसका सुरक्षित रहना हमारी दया से होगा। और यह उसकी दया और रक्षा है कि इस मानव संसार में किसी धार्मिक ग्रंथ के संबंध में यह दावा नहीं किया जा सकता कि वह सुरक्षित है, यह गौरव केवल क़ुरआन ही को प्राप्त है।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wanuyassiruka lil'yus'rā ","translations":["And We will ease you","to the ease","(8)"],"transliterationArr":["wanuyassiruka","lil'yus'rā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1510],[2,1510,3285]]}},{"name":"87:9","price":"तो आप नसीहत करते रहें। अगर नसीहत करना लाभदायक हो।","arabic":"فَذَكِّرۡ إِن نَّفَعَتِ ٱلذِّكۡرَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5957,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fadhakkir in nafaʿati al-dhik'rā ","translations":["So remind","if","benefits","the reminder","(9)"],"transliterationArr":["fadhakkir","in","nafaʿati","al-dhik'rā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,950],[2,950,1300],[3,1300,3070],[4,3070,4835]]}},{"name":"87:10","price":"वह व्यक्ति उपदेश ग्रहण करेगा, जो डरता है।","arabic":"سَيَذَّكَّرُ مَن يَخۡشَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5958,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"sayadhakkaru man yakhshā ","translations":["He will pay heed ","(one) who","fears (Allah)","(10)"],"transliterationArr":["sayadhakkaru","man","yakhshā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1660],[2,1660,1900],[3,1900,4095]]}},{"name":"87:11","price":"और उससे दूर रहेगा, जो सबसे बड़ा अभागा है।","arabic":"وَيَتَجَنَّبُهَا ٱلۡأَشۡقَى","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5959,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wayatajannabuhā al-ashqā ","translations":["And will avoid it","the wretched one","(11)"],"transliterationArr":["wayatajannabuhā","al-ashqā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2420],[2,2420,4215]]}},{"name":"87:12","price":"जो सबसे बड़ी आग में प्रवेश करेगा।","arabic":"ٱلَّذِي يَصۡلَى ٱلنَّارَ ٱلۡكُبۡرَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5960,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"alladhī yaṣlā al-nāra al-kub'rā ","translations":["The one who","will burn","(in) the Fire","[the] great","(12)"],"transliterationArr":["alladhī","yaṣlā","al-nāra","al-kub'rā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1120],[2,1120,1680],[3,1680,3400],[4,3400,5055]]}},{"name":"87:13","price":"फिर वह उसमें न मरेगा, न जिएगा।[4]","arabic":"ثُمَّ لَا يَمُوتُ فِيهَا وَلَا يَحۡيَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5961,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"4. (9-13) इनमें बताया गया है कि आपको मात्र इसका प्रचार-प्रसार करना है। और इसकी सरल राह यह है कि जो सुने और मानने के लिए तैयार हो, उसे शिक्षा दी जाए। किसी के पीछे पड़ने की आवश्यकता नहीं है। जो हत्भागे हैं, वही नहीं सुनेंगे और नरक की यातना के रूप में अपना दुष्परिणाम देखेंगे।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"thumma lā yamūtu fīhā walā yaḥyā ","translations":["Then","not","he will die","therein","and not","will live","(13)"],"transliterationArr":["thumma","lā","yamūtu","fīhā","walā","yaḥyā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1650],[2,1650,2180],[3,2180,3100],[4,3100,4010],[5,4010,4740],[6,4740,5865]]}},{"name":"87:14","price":"निश्चय वह सफल हो गया, जो पाक हो गया।","arabic":"قَدۡ أَفۡلَحَ مَن تَزَكَّىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5962,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"qad aflaḥa man tazakkā ","translations":["Certainly","has succeeded","(one) who","purifies (himself)","(14)"],"transliterationArr":["qad","aflaḥa","man","tazakkā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,350],[2,350,1250],[3,1250,2400],[4,2400,3865]]}},{"name":"87:15","price":"तथा अपने पालनहार के नाम को याद किया और नमाज़ पढ़ी।[5]","arabic":"وَذَكَرَ ٱسۡمَ رَبِّهِۦ فَصَلَّىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5963,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"5. (14-15) इन आयतों में कहा गया है कि सफलता मात्र उनके लिए है, जो आस्था, स्वभाव तथा कर्म की पवित्रता को अपनाएँ, और नमाज़ अदा करते रहें।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wadhakara is'ma rabbihi faṣallā ","translations":["And remembers","(the) name","(of) his Lord","and prays","(15)"],"transliterationArr":["wadhakara","is'ma","rabbihi","faṣallā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,790],[2,790,1290],[3,1290,2390],[4,2390,3635]]}},{"name":"87:16","price":"बल्कि तुम सांसारिक जीवन को प्राथमिकता देते हो।","arabic":"بَلۡ تُؤۡثِرُونَ ٱلۡحَيَوٰةَ ٱلدُّنۡيَا","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5964,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"bal tu'thirūna al-ḥayata al-dun'yā ","translations":["Nay","You prefer","the life","(of) the world","(16)"],"transliterationArr":["bal","tu'thirūna","al-ḥayata","al-dun'yā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,410],[2,410,1620],[3,1620,2760],[4,2760,4015]]}},{"name":"87:17","price":"हालाँकि आख़िरत बहुत उत्तम और अधिक बाक़ी रहने वाली है।","arabic":"وَٱلۡأٓخِرَةُ خَيۡرٞ وَأَبۡقَىٰٓ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5965,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wal-ākhiratu khayrun wa-abqā ","translations":["While the Hereafter","(is) better","and everlasting","(17)"],"transliterationArr":["wal-ākhiratu","khayrun","wa-abqā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1580],[2,1580,3190],[3,3190,4805]]}},{"name":"87:18","price":"निःसंदेह यह बात पहले सह़ीफ़ों (ग्रंथों) में है।","arabic":"إِنَّ هَٰذَا لَفِي ٱلصُّحُفِ ٱلۡأُولَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5966,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"inna hādhā lafī al-ṣuḥufi al-ūlā ","translations":["Indeed","this","surely (is) in","the Scriptures","[the] former","(18)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","hādhā","lafī","al-ṣuḥufi","al-ūlā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1460],[2,1460,2360],[3,2360,2740],[4,2740,3700],[5,3700,4865]]}},{"name":"87:19","price":"इबराहीम तथा मूसा के सह़ीफ़ों (ग्रंथों) में।[6]","arabic":"صُحُفِ إِبۡرَٰهِيمَ وَمُوسَىٰ","category":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la"],"ayahNumber":5967,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"6. (16-19) इन आयतों का भावार्थ यह है कि वास्तव में रोग यह है कि काफ़िरों को सांसारिक स्वार्थ के कारण नबी की बातें अच्छी नहीं लगतीं। जबकि परलोक ही स्थायी है। और यही सभी आदि ग्रंथों की शिक्षा है।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"ṣuḥufi ib'rāhīma wamūsā ","translations":["(The) Scriptures","(of) Ibrahim","and Musa","(19)"],"transliterationArr":["ṣuḥufi","ib'rāhīma","wamūsā",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,830],[2,830,2360],[3,2360,4025]]}}],"chapter":["87 (Al-A'la)","Al-A'la","Surah Al-A'la","Chapter Al-A'la","A'la","Surah A'la","Chapter A'la","Al A'la","Surah Al A'la","Chapter Al A'la","Surah 87","Chapter 87","The Most High","الأعلى"],"version":{"key":"hindi_omari","direction":"ltr","language_iso_code":"hi","version":"1.1.4","last_update":1675069101,"title":"Hindi Translation","description":"Translation of the Quran meanings into Indian by Azizul-Haqq Al-Umary."}}